WEBVTT
NOTE OE3D — Script1 — English

1
00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:01.484
Hello!

2
00:00:01.434 --> 00:00:05.138
I am your orthotist-prosthetist at Ortho Espace 3D in French Guiana.

3
00:00:05.138 --> 00:00:09.502
Your custom orthosis or prosthesis is a precious medical device.

4
00:00:09.502 --> 00:00:13.655
To keep it effective for a long time, here are some simple daily routines.

5
00:00:15.055 --> 00:00:16.608
Cleaning.

6
00:00:16.558 --> 00:00:20.739
Wipe your device every day with a slightly damp cloth and mild soap.

7
00:00:20.739 --> 00:00:22.734
Avoid immersing it in water.

8
00:00:22.734 --> 00:00:26.449
Let it air dry, never near a heat source.

9
00:00:27.849 --> 00:00:29.589
Wearing and friction.

10
00:00:29.539 --> 00:00:32.488
Follow your practitioner's recommendations.

11
00:00:32.488 --> 00:00:34.509
Take regular breaks.

12
00:00:34.509 --> 00:00:38.971
If you notice persistent redness or friction, contact us promptly.

13
00:00:40.371 --> 00:00:41.963
Monitoring.

14
00:00:41.913 --> 00:00:44.480
Regularly inspect your device.

15
00:00:44.480 --> 00:00:48.830
If you feel new pain or discomfort, contact us right away.

16
00:00:50.230 --> 00:00:51.631
Storage.

17
00:00:51.581 --> 00:00:55.194
Store your device away from heat and humidity.

18
00:00:55.194 --> 00:00:58.185
Avoid impacts that could deform its structure.

19
00:00:59.585 --> 00:01:01.431
Liner care.

20
00:01:01.381 --> 00:01:05.724
If you wear a prosthesis, wash your liner every evening with water and mild soap.

21
00:01:05.724 --> 00:01:08.271
Turn it inside out to dry in the open air.

22
00:01:08.271 --> 00:01:10.767
Plan for a replacement every six months.

23
00:01:12.167 --> 00:01:16.121
If in doubt, our team is available by phone or WhatsApp.

24
00:01:16.071 --> 00:01:17.575
Take care!
